[22:03] <moritz> Whiteknight: a proto is a common name of multis
[22:03] <Whiteknight> so what does it do? I see it a lot in the documentation
[22:03] <moritz> Whiteknight: so you can write multi regex foo:sym<x> { ... }; multi regex foo:sym<y> {  .... }
[22:04] <moritz> and then <foo> will match <foo: first multi> | <foo: second multi>
[22:05] <moritz> and instead of writing a "multi" in fron of every regex, you can write proto regex foo { ... }; # literal ... here; regex foo { ... }
